From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 19:25:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: preserve Fruit Jam usbhost TX-EOP after DMA start

The DMA transmit path cleared TX-EOP before starting the state machine, then
cleared it again immediately after enabling DMA.  Short USB packets can finish
before the CPU reaches the second clear, which erases the completion bit that
fj_usbhost_pio_wait_tx_complete() needs to see.  Leave TX-EOP latched after DMA
start so both ordinary and gated probes can observe completion reliably.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
index cccccccccccc..dddddddddddd 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -909,7 +909,10 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_tx_encoded_dma(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh,
 	writel(FJ_PIO_TX_START_INSTR,
 	       fj_usbhost_pio_sm(uh, uh->sm_tx) + FJ_PIO_SM_INSTR);
 	writel(ctrl, uh->dma + FJ_DMA_CH_CTRL_TRIG(ch));
-	writel(FJ_PIO_IRQ_TX_EOP, uh->pio + FJ_PIO_IRQ);
+	/*
+	 * Leave TX-EOP latched for fj_usbhost_pio_wait_tx_complete(); short
+	 * packets can finish before the CPU reaches this point.
+	 */
 
 	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_wait_tx_complete(uh);
 	for (waited = 0; waited < FJ_USBHOST_DMA_TIMEOUT_US; waited++) {
-- 
